  ],
  "behavior": "I hesitate to speak up or share my ideas during the discussion. I avoid making any commitments or decisions about my future plans. I might withdraw from the conversation or seek reassurance from my parents.",
  "rationale": "\"The patient may feel tense and apprehensive about their financial future and the implications of their current situation... This dependency could also evoke feelings of shame or embarrassment, as relying on parents for financial support might conflict with their desire for independence and self-sufficiency.\" \"The discussion about future plans might prompt the patient to engage in 'catastrophizing,' imagining worst-case scenarios regarding their career and financial stability.\" \"They might withdraw from discussions with family members to avoid conflict or feelings of inadequacy. The patient could also seek reassurance from their parents, despite the discomfort it may cause, as a way to cope with their anxiety.\""
